Extend EDR coverage to all endpoints.

4. ğŸ” Identity and Access Management (IAM)
4.1 Authentication
Internal systems use LDAP without TLS encryption: âŒ
SaaS services (e.g., Google Workspace, Salesforce) secured with SSO: âœ…
Shared root/admin credentials found in DevOps team: âŒ
4.2 Authorization
RBAC implemented only on cloud dashboard: âŒ
No least-privilege enforcement on AWS IAM policies: âŒ
4.3 Account Lifecycle
Former employees still have active credentials (2 of 15): âŒ
No automated de-provisioning process: âŒ
4.4 Recommendations
Encrypt LDAP authentication (LDAPS).
Enforce password rotation and eliminate shared accounts.
Audit IAM roles and enable least privilege on cloud resources.


5. ğŸ§± Web Applications & APIs
5.1 Web Applications (Customer Portal, Internal CRM)
No WAF in place for production portal: âŒ
Internal CRM allows admin page access without auth token: âŒ
Input fields not sanitized â€“ potential for XSS and SQL injection: âŒ

5.2 APIs
Public REST API lacks authentication for GET endpoints: âŒ
No rate limiting or API gateway: âŒ
Uses outdated JWT libraries (vulnerable to token forgery): âŒ
5.3 Recommendations
Implement WAF with OWASP rule sets.
Sanitize all user inputs and use parameterized queries.
Migrate to updated JWT libraries and secure API endpoints with API keys and OAuth2.


